    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Malaise, anorexia,\nmyalgias\n,\narthralgias\n,\nfever\n, painful skin, GI symptoms\nExtracutaneous manifestations may persist for 1-2 weeks following skin symptoms\nExam with warm tender erythema with overlying flaccid\nbullae\n, erosions with exfoliation\nPositive Nikolsky's sign (able to rub off superficial layers of skin with pressure)\nMucosal involvement (oral, conjunctival, respiratory, GU)\nSystemic toxicity\n25-35% Mortality\nDeath is usually caused by\ninfection\n,\nhypovolemia\n, and\nelectrolyte disorders\nPredictors of poor prognosis include: age, extent of disease,\nleukopenia\n, azotemia, and\nthrombocytopenia",
